caption: Fantastic service and food. A great atmosphere.

The scallops are fork tender and the draft list seemed more unique then the average Chicago bar/restaurant. My partner ordered a medium steak but unfortunately it was a little under done. The bartender was quick to offer a dessert to make up for it. Definitely want to come back and try the other menu options! Great cocktails :)

I live a block away and have been here a few times.  I like to support local but I don't know what happened to this place. The food,service and atmosphere where great but when I stopped by this morning the service was terrible.  I had ordered carryout and walked over to pick it up and they pretty much ignored me when I could see it behind the hostesses. I was waiting at the bar to pay and was ignored by the bartender. The place was half empty. I come home to see that they messed up my order... The staff really needs to get it together here, there were rude and aloof.
Wonderful restaurant, great food, incredible atmosphere, beautiful decorations. You must see the bar in the basement.

Popped in with no reservation on a Tuesday night 9pm.  Thankful to be accepted in although wait staff wasn’t very attentive probably due to the end of a night.  Salad was great, cocktail “Willow” and flourless chocolate cake were okay, and pasta was light in flavor.  Will be an excellent venue for people who like simple pure true food flavors.  Appreciated the staff monetarily anyways!  Thanks for having me the last minute.
Excellent food, great drinks, great place for date night. Not cheap but top quality food and service. Cool mix of seafood, steak, other options. Highly recommend and worth the trip.
I waited a very long time to have beef Wellington and I'm happy to had it.
Haven’t been during the pandemic but before the pandemic they had the most amazing atmosphere. The food was great and the cocktails are amazing!

Service was fantastic. Servers and bussers all work very hard to keep patrons safe but give pleasant and attentive service. The greenhouse/igloo experience was great and very well managed.  Food was a bit pricey, especially for portion size of the meals, but still good overall.  Jamon croquettes were alright, perhaps a bit bland.  Crab ceasar salad was a very delicious and unique offering, though know that the "old bay chips" are literally chips, like ruffles. It took some getting used to...  Lobster ravioli was OK. The ravioli itself was very good, though didn't get many with the meal. The sauce was very lemony and acidic, but still overall a good dish.  The espresso martini was fantastic. The doughnuts were tasty, not overwhelmingly sweet.  All in all, the food was good and the experience was great, will definitely return to try some other dishes.
Such a great neighborhood spot. Came for the vibes, stayed for the risotto.
Everything we ordered was both delicious and unique!

Was a cold one, but the greenhouse broke the window and kept in some of the heat from the heater.  The Burrata, Lobster Ravioli, and the Steak Diane were top-notch (although the Lobster Ravioli was a very small dish). Our waitress was a trooper even in the bitter cold. I would definitely recommend!
Fantastic service and food in a great atmosphere. The beef wellington and steak diane were mouth watering!

I review lots of restaurants because it helps all of us. I use reviews to decide where I want to eat. If your looking at this place, book with confidence! I love this area of Chicago so this is extra good. This place has great atmosphere but the food is up to the task. A small but interesting menu. The new Risotto which was just put on the menu that night was sensational. I had the bone marrow, something I particularly like and this was great. One of our group also had the bone in ribeye and also the butternut squash cannelloni. I found no faults. The wine list is competent. Give it a try.
Really cute space, the food was pretty good and came out very quickly. Service was great. Only downside was that the food is pretty standard fare American food, tasty though.
Greenhouse was a fantastic experience!!
Loved the outdoor dining experience.
Came here for date night ! Monica our server was awesome and the igloos were warmer than expected despite it snowing ! Amazing wine selection and cute aesthetic ! Will be back again soon !
The outside greenhouses are really great and the food and service was great also.
Great
Great food. The burger is really good. They have COVID-19 safe plastic huts that have heaters.
Great date night. Great spot for family dinner event. Delicious food, nice atmosphere, great wait staff!. Highly  recommended!! :)
Excellent place for COVID dining. The outdoor greenhouses are really nice and cozy.

Nice igloos outside! Service is always excellent and the drinks/food are great! Can't wait for the indoor to be open again soon. Great brunch options - needs more gluten free options but plenty of good things to choose from!
Outdoor dining in the glass house is a great experience. Heaters keep you warm
Ordered takeout from Willow Room today and the food was spectacularly good! Unpretentious but very high quality and flavorful dishes. We’ll be doing this again!
lovely new spot ... we were attracted first by the cute greenhouse tents but then by the menu which really delivered!! venture forth, you won't be sorry
Came here often for the short rib. After they told me it wasn’t on the lunch menu, and I could not order it they served it to the guys sitting next to me. Lost my business  -Very disappointed

Came in with high expectations that were unfortunately not met. My girlfriend and I shared the Monday $36 three course meal, with an order of burrata on the side. The burrata was one-note and overly sweet, I would recommend adding some nuts or seeds to add textural variety. The panzanella was genuinely good - I enjoyed the combination of flavors between the vinaigrette and pickled onions. The short rib was tender, though it needed more flavor. The cheesecake was okay but, again, fairly unremarkable.  Overall, another classic example of a Chicago New American restaurant which is fine but does not impress.

Have been here only for lunch  and dinner and it's absolutely delicious! Bees knees cocktail is so refreshing with a good hearty brunch. Bone marrow is some of the best in town and the beignets are so addicting. Great decor, and service too!
Great brunch in a greenhouse. We felt safe and they followed covid rules for cleaning and serving awesome food 👌
Who knew such a chill lovely spot was tucked away on this little street.  10/10.  The donuts and Crab salad are 🔥
The cooker does a excellent job the meal comes out so excellent
Cute ambiance! Good food. Would go back again.
Great food, great service, great decor! All around wonderful dining experience!
Great food, great entertainment, great service

They were so nice to me. I was out Enumerating and they let me sit down and do notes for work. It was so hot outside - they even gave me water. After work, I went back for the Hamachi and some Cremant - both were amazing. The other food shuttling to the other guest also looked yummy.

Food was great and the service was spot on.  I called to move our reservation inside as the forecast was not looking good for later that evening and the staff was very accommodating. Turned out to be a good move as it rained for the firat half hour plus that we were there. The menu is accessed via QR code and the tables were sufficiently distanced.  The menu is somewhat upscale but the burger at the table next to us looked fantastic so those looking for simpler fare should be well served.  All-in-all a very nice dinner and I would happily recommend you give it a try.
Great service and ambiance! The stake tartar was phenomenal and the old fashion fantastic!
Lovely atmosphere indoors and outdoors, great patio, very friendly wait staff, good food and drinks! Will definitely be coming back!

I love a restaurant with a bee's knees! It's my favorite drink and was fantastic. I had the scallops that our waiter Murphy said was delicious and it had the perfect blend of flavors. The chefs are great here and I'm so delighted that I live near by and can't wait to come back!
Great place, I love their salmon dish! will definitely come back!

i had such a great time today at willow room. the food came out extremely fast. we were sat right away at 11am without reservation the server just kindly told us that they had another table in an hour. highly recommend the waldorf salad and french dip.... broccoli i... it was all spectacular. the drinks were priced well, and the pours were hefty! a beautiful treat for us to enjoy. great service! in my opinion, better music, service and food than summer house!
I had the avocado toast and my boyfriend had the chiliquiles, both were fabulous!

I visited Willow Room yesterday and I was highly impressed with the service I received. I’m a new vegan and I tried to order some vegan friendly food. The waiter told the chef and he personally came to my table and told me that what I ordered wasn’t 100% vegan and that he would make me a vegan dish. THAT DISH WAS SOOOO GOOD!! I highly recommend you visit this establishment.
thank you for a splendid Mother's Day brunch! the leftovers are going to be great later ✌🏼

We just had their short ribs and potatoes last night and it was so good we just had to get it again for Easter dinner. We got their half chicken, scallop potatoes, brussel sprouts and bread pudding and everything was perfect. Thank you willow room for getting us through the quarantine!

I hosted a private event of 30+ people as a surprise engagement party, for my now fiancé. The Willow Room staff was so helpful in organizing the event and surprising my fiancé! Matt was very quick to respond to all of my emails and the staff the day of were very personable and helpful! The food was some of the best I have had in the city and the drinks were amazing! Everyone at the party couldn’t stop talking about how delicious the cocktails were- and we have a hard group to please! Overall we are so happy with the service provided at Willow Room and will definitely be going back for further parties and events!
Great burger.

Too small portions and too expensive for what you get. I have been to more expensive and fancier restaurants than this and the quality/price ratio was not this low. Please avoid and try another place in this nice neighborhood.
Good brunch, good drinks, okay service. Nothing was outstanding, so kinda meh. Cocktails had more sugar than flavor.
Food was good. Halibut and brussel sprouts are amazing. Service was okay and table by the door is quite drafty. Worth it if you get a more secluded table and different service!!
Nice
Awesome spot. Cool owners
The place is excellent. Have been there for dinner and now brunch. Food is amazing and the service is fantastic. Plan to go back many times.

I had dinner here with my partner and it was overall a great meal. I particularly enjoyed the burrata and beef wellington (which we shared). It came with sides of potatoes and brussel sprouts. The potatoes were really good, brussel sprouts were the only thing I didn't really care for. They had crushed peanut on them, which I thought was unusual and I was very interested in trying it out, but....meh. Felt like it stuck to the roof of my mouth (but please do not add jelly!).  And maybe not a big deal, but I found the way the menu was written to be annoyingly pretentious. Why write pommes pure when you can write whipped or mashed potatoes? Maybe they're going for fancy, but it's obnoxious and inaccessible.
We stopped in for restaurant week and were not disappointed!! The hollandaise was incredible and I love the variety of mimosas offered! Can't wait to come back 😋
Disagree with the 4.5 rating, it was clearly a 5.
Exquisite gourmet food!
Amazing food, staff really friendly and helpful. Had the pork belly and it was delicious.
Very good food and service but a little pricey!

last night was the first time we visited this good restaurant. But It is obviously not the last time. We had great time with the attentive service, with the magnificent  dishes and wine and with the honest payment. We will no doubt return there in a short time.
The portions were small.  The dishes were cold, and the entrees were bland at best.
Service was fantastic, food was delicious and had wonderful, complex flavors. Drinks were delicious with unexpected flavors. The brussel sprouts are a must!

Great decor and amazing food. We order 5 appetizers and we were SO full. The octopus and salad was my favorite. They gave us bread to dip into to burrata and mussels and the sauce was so good we wanted to drink it. Can’t wait to go back!!

Very good cocktails and wine list. The food was quite good, especially the mussels and the various pastas. Service was spot on, friendly and prompt. The only minor complaint is the space itself - it's pretty loud. Otherwise had a good experience and would go back.
Excellent food and service!!
Delicious meal, delightful staff!

We have had brunch there a couple times in the food is pretty good in the restaurant is hustling. On a Monday night we were the only customers and the service was still slow. After being seated for 5 minutes, and again we were the only table, I had to get up and look for the server so we could order a drink. The steak tartare and the butternut squash cannellini we're both fairly bland. The s'mores dessert was really not edible. Will be back for brunch only!
This place is for real! Great staff! Great service! A Chicago must do!

Stopped in for lunch on Saturday and the place was full.  It's a great room.  Lots of natural light and a nice relaxed vibe...with good tunes at the perfect volume.  I found a spot at the bar and had a bloody- delicious!  Had a burger and it was excellent.  Service was attentive and friendly.   I would highly recommend this place and I will be back.
Service is great! Love the food! Steak tartare was awesome!
Tasty brunch options with excellent and friendly service by Bernadette.
Really amazing atmosphere, don't forget to checkout the cozy downstairs bar.
Nice place
Pleasant vibe. Staff is attentive without being intrusive. Had a good burger but, really, American cheese :(

The menu is eclectic and pretty small, but that allows them to execute it all well. The staff are great, the ambiance is nice and you will love the food. They also have some good weekday specials you should check out.

Food was pretty good. Went with a group and shared a bunch of dishes between us. Everything was delicious. Cocktails were pretty good too. Tuesdays is half off all wine bottles so definitely take advantage of that.
Had a great lunch.  Must try the Mac& Cheese.

Our family had an excellent dinner together. Wait staff was excellent and attentive. The meals were delicious and wonderfully prepared and seasoned. Definitely would recommend this restaurant to others looking for a comfortable dining experience and diverse menu.
The bone in pork chop was great.  I asked for the pork medium rare and it was perfectly cook.  Probably top 5 as far as pork chops are concerned.  The brussel sprouts and halibut were fantastic also
Great service great food.expensice wine
Food was very nice, though service outside can be a bit disattended at some points..
Awsome brunch!
Charming place with very good food!
Expensive and fine
Small menu
We happened upon Willow after a little league game and it was perfect. Food is delicious. Staff attentive and nice. Outdoor seating a must!
Go here at least twice a month
Really good food overall, surprised by how delicious the bone marrows are. However, the bread that came with them is bit burnt, which was a shame. Other than that, rather perfect dinner
Good
My favorite brunch place in the city!

The wait staff is the best here. So accommodating and friendly! The food was outstanding - fair prices for some very good flavor! I choose the Eggs Benedict and it did not disappoint. Asked for a side of mayonnaise and was blown away by the fresh flavor - tastes homemade.
Amazing, delicious food. Engaging and friendly staff.
Get the red velvet corner booth. Food is excellent. Gorgeous atmosphere. Lively and not pretentious.
Ready fast

This would have been 5*s but our server was  "having an off night"  I really like this place.  Walked from Front Bar to have dinner before heading back to Steppenwolf for BLKS.  Wife had the 1/4 chicken and I had some clam pasta dish.  Great food, great drinks, nice atmosphere.
Quiet outdoor summer eating. Great aviation cocktail!
Pork belly hash was great but small portion
Food was delicious but service on a Monday night was slow.  Beautiful restaurant
Service was fast, the food was good and price was moderate.
One word: Yummy!
Great spot for brunch! Food was fantastic, especially the donuts. Good space for groups and families. New go-to spot for us.
Service was friendly, and the menu interesting and exceptionally delicious. Who knew broccolini could taste so good?! I hope to go back sometime for the champagne and fries.

Checked out the Willow Room for brunch on Saturday. The ambiance and feel of the place is very relaxing. Lots of sunlight and open seating area makes for good vibes. Can be a little loud at times and the food was a little bit salty but I would go back again!
Nice environment good food
Friendly staff, great food, get the burger.
Jen was the best server ever. She needs a raise!!!!
Excellent! Love love love.
A slightly limited menu (for me), however, I got the Turkey Club, which may sound simple, but was one of the best I've ever had.

Great food and service for our large group of 30. The appetizers (meat and cheese plates, bread and mozzarella and truffle fries) were fresh and tasty. Also had the Gnocchi with mushrooms which was so flavorful and perfectly cooked. Also tried the Lamb, which I wish I would have ordered,as the flavor was phenomenal. Highly recommend this restaurant for your family or large get together. They have a nice cellar room that worked perfectly for our group.
Small menu, big flavor, top notch service.
Brilliant!
Great place for a brunch with friends! The food was good, I loved the Salmon Bagel. And the staff was very welcoming and attentive.
had restaurant week $49 pre fix pre steppenwolf. All good. Warm and classy, comfortable space. Sunday eve early no resv. no complaints. So many good places to eat in Chicago
A great atmosphere for a romantic dinner with your significant other. Prices are a bit high but it's worth, the food is outstanding.
Murphy is the best. I hear he was a great baseball player. Love the desserts (that's all I had)
Cute place, went for brunch during Restaurant Week. Good service, pancakes were delicious!

Been twice, once during restaurant week, the attention to detail and service was outstanding, portions were large, everything was delicious! 2nd course was a potato leek soup. I’m not a soup person and this was SO GOOD!

Went here for dinner on my birthday after seeing it and telling my boyfriend it looked cute. We were the only table there so service was fine, but impersonal. The burger was recommended and it tasted ok but was extremely greasy and I got sick immediately after the dinner. Called to warn them that the meat must have been bad and they just said thank you. A quick apology later and nothing was offered to make up for getting sick on my birthday.
Really good neighborhood restaurant. I enjoyed the risotto and the Willow salad  The prix fixe menu on Mondays is a great deal. Save room for dessert!
Gorgeous restaurant, love the atmosphere and the drinks & menu are both outstanding!

Amazing food! I didn't have any expectations going into it since I was unfamiliar with the restaurant (despite being in the area many times) and it's already a place to return to for me. Every single thing we got was delicious, from the drinks to the food. The interior of the restaurant is extremely fun and cozy while still feeling upscale. Can't wait to go back!
First time here and noticed they do brunch on Thursday through Sunday. Great atmosphere and good food.
Amazing staff, friendly service. Get here now,  you won't regret it.

We had a work event here. It was hosted in the basement room. The drink menu was extensive and the wine list and beer list were impressive. The food was good but not great. Should be noted that we had a set menu though. The atmosphere was warm and inviting. If the food were a little better, would be five stars. Do recommend.
"Good music and bustling energy."Great food dishes.
One of our favorites in the city.   Great team great food.
Outstanding. One of our new top Chicago faves.
Good high scale American food. I would recommend if you wanted a nice dinner with family and friends. Cozy atmosphere, high price point.
Good food. Fast servive. Very noiay

Yes very good Muscles were OK..  Could have been bigger..portion was very good. Hamachi app very very good Caesar Salad with scallops OK Scallops very very good. Service very attentive Price mid point reasonable
Food and drinks were awful. The pork was chewy and flavorless,  and the bone marrow had very little marrow. The cocktail tasted medicinal. The service was good, but I wouldn’t return.
Delicious! We tried 4 things from the menu (beef tartar, brussel sprouts, octopus, and a spinach pasta), and wanted to try everything else. Will hopefully be back soon.
Upscale dining without all the pressure in a fantastic atmosphere. Menu changes often so don’t try to pick one favorite.
Classy music, beautiful dining hall and bustling energy.

The food is fresh and tasty and the fried chicken sandwich and biscuits and gravy were delicious. This is a really nice place to bring family or friends for a nice but casual brunch. The service was exceptional and all the staff were beyond accommodating. Definitely stop by if you are in the area.
Went for Sunday brunch with a group of friends. The food was great (had the burger) but the service was even better. Will definitely return next time I am in Chicago. :)
Wonderful cocktail list and dinner menu.  Great for sharing.
Outstanding customer service.
Good food in a spacious environment. Servers are attentive but not overbearing. Great for Steppenwolf pre-play dining.
Excellent and unusual brunch choices that were superb in taste and presentation! Highly recommend!

Loved their monday special for $30. 1st course - meat and cheese, and mussels were great 2nd course - steak, scallops, and chicken were great 3rd course - strawberry shortcake was the best (I didn’t like the coffee whatever - too much cream) Service was great!
This place is amazing. Food is great, drinks are delicious and the service is second to none! Very kid friendly. Regular go to for my family!
Great brunch, love the mimosa options
I was there once and unjoy time. Great food and nice atmosphere
Food was really good - good variety and fun brunch drinks
Great food, great Vibe! get the Wings! they are incredible. I would suggest just sticking to appetizers.
Great food and drinks!
Theeeeeeee Bomb fresh squeezed citrus juice in Chicago! Food was....meh
always nice to eat and drink here. The burger is actually one of the best in the city IMO. Flat iron is great too. Cocktails are great and super nice vibe in place.

We loved it.  Went for mother's day and of course reserved our table ahead of time.  The servers were incredibly helpful and patient Regardless of our large group.  So enough about us, how about the food...  So with all the people in our group I can say that almost the entire menu had been ordered and everyone in our group was very impressed.  I ordered the Avocado toast and was surprised to see the immensity of the plate for what I'd expected to be simply a  couple pieces of decorated bread and avocado.  Dang was it tasty.  Totally recommend trying it.  I'm posting pictures of the lights as it was the only pictures managed to take and only becausy fiance likes them.  I give the Willow Room 2 thumbs up for service and flavor.
Great food,  defiantly get the Korean chicken wings and an old fashion.

It was just what we wanted after leaving the Steppenwolf. Nice but not too full of itself. The people were very friendly. The menu is simply there to please...there are zero surprises but they cared about what they served.
Had a nice meal with a family, including little kids and everything was great. From high cuisine to burgers it was all excellent.
Great food and service
Get the burger. Great beer and cocktail list.  Very expensive, but worth it. Great service.
Great food and service. Very accommodating with food sensitivities.
Great interior, wine list, menu
Good wine list, delicious food, nice atmosphere and friendly wait staff.

I went here on NYE w my gf for their fixed menu.  It's was awesome.  We were seated downstairs and the bartender immediately greeted us and got us drinks.  The food was fantastic.  In sum, well priced, delicious, and excellent service.
The burrata, vongole, and burger were fantastic. Great service too.
Discovered this place while driving by.. relaxed atmosphere and amazing brunch drinks.. do try the Korean fried chicken sandwich.. a amazing burst of flavors!
Great location and atmosphere , but the food was awful.  Eggs were so runny, corn beef has was mostly fat and burgers were so greasy.  They need a new cook!

I found the Willow Room when I was looking for a dinner option before a show at Steppenwolf. Nice lighting and atmosphere, cozy, and friendly. A little noisy, but a good place for a date. Everything on the menu looked good, but we were in the mood for burgers, so that’s what we ordered along with beer, cocktails, and a salad. I felt a little funny ordering burgers at an upscale restaurant, but they were exceptional. Double patty, American cheese and dijonnaise on a brioche bun with fries. The salad and cocktails were great as well. We had to order the burgers again on our next visit. So good.
Murph is a great bartender.  Stop in.
Great private room downstairs. Old fashioneds are awesome.

Brunch was fantastic. I had the avocado toast with a side salad - it was delicious and refreshing. My table mates had the chilaquiles and the two egg breakfast, both well reviewed. You have to get the breakfast potatoes - they are the best I’ve had in the city!
We had an incredibly friendly bar tender. He made great suggestions and was very friendly. The interior is beautiful and the food smelled amazing. Excellent date spot.

I was seated in the basement which felt more like a sports bar than an upscale restaurant. Everything - and I mean everything - on the menu was cool five years ago. Hamachi crudo? Bone marrow? Yawn...they didn't even pretend to be innovative or fresh. I gave it one extra star for the solid martini.

Missed the mark...  Service was mediocre and the menu needs a bit of polishing.  The avocado toast was on the bland side. The toast itself was burnt and difficult to eat with a very thick, chewy crust.
Great menu and service. Loved their burger!
Food was good but overpriced for what you get.
Great drinks here but last time I went they closed early
Amazing atmosphere and attentive staff. Great selections recommendations by staff. The food was delicious!
Great ambiance, service and food!! Looking forward to coming back!!

AMBIANCE: The vintage light bulb bordered windows and hanging orb lights make Willow Room an extremely classy and chic restaurant. Absolutely ideal for a dinner date night or girls' night out. Classy music, beautiful dining hall and bustling energy.  FOOD: For starters, the carpaccio is out of this world delicious. Must get. Every thinly sliced beef is coated with olive oil, pepper and pecorino. The arugula green and shaved egg yolk complements its rich taste profile. The rainbow trout is also another winner. Though the malt vinegar overwhelms an otherwise aromatic brown butter sauce, the trout is presented beautifully with vivid pop of colors from the green peas and bull blood micro greens.
Nice Lincoln Park spot for brunch.  The food is varied, although traditional brunch items are available.  Try the cauliflower - outstanding.  Service is good, but the place can get very loud.

The Willow Room is a new find for us when visiting Chicago. Food really great, cocktails are perfect and the staff is really attentive. Plus Elvis came in for brunch and performed as well. I can't wait to go back for dinner.
Overall great dinning experience...this is the place. The atmosphere made it easy to enjoy more than a few cocktails

We were walking in the neighborhood on a Saturday evening after a play at the nearby theater and decided to give The Willow Room a shot. The hostesses greeted us in a very friendly manner and almost immediately had us a nice table in the window. The restaurant is well done in a visual sense, airy, old brick, lots of well placed and interesting art. There is also a dining room in the basement that I checked put and would certainly be a nice cozy spot for a romantic dinner date. Then...it went all wrong. We were given menus and water but no server addressed us for over 10 mins. Suddenly a food runner appears with an order of Burrata and sets it down and walks away. My wife tried to call someone over and they ignored us. So she began eating it, it was her birthday and we were hungry travelers. It was a great Burrata. A server comes to the table with a harried look about her and asks "did you order this?" My wife says, "nope, but it is really delicious and just put it on our bill". The server says nothing more and walks away. The runner appears at the neighboring table with another order of Burrata and another appetizer, the couple says they didn't order the Burrata but did the other. We looked at one another and knew something was not going well here. Finally our server comes, introduces herself and asks if we want to order. 25mins after seating. We order: soup and the trout special for my wife. I am out of sorts at this point, little sounds good so I order the shrimp/crab cocktail appetizer and a cheeseburger/fries that sounds like tasty and easy out. Fortunately, my wife is enjoying her wine and Burrata, the place has good energy from the patrons. Our server doesn't reappear for ages, the runner and another server top off my water and check on my lady's wine. L's soup appetizer arrives....as does my dinner. Server finally appeared again "I am soo sorry...I uh...didn't understand...I am not sure why this came out this way...do you want me to hold this for you?" um no. I will just eat it now and have my appetizer for dinner. She walks away befuddled and my wife and I are as well. Burger and fries are tasty, lots of fries, good bun, little bit light anf thin patties but they were delicious. L likes her beet soup very much. The trout dinner shows up. It is a very handsome and fragrant plate, a generous filet of trout. L is delighted. I am slowly eating so I don't out pace her. Server swings by if all was okay. I said yes, good food and whenever the kitchen has my appetizer done I will take it. (we hadn't eaten since 930am and had walked all day) We finish what we have and wait. Server asks if we want to see a dessert menu, we do just for kicks. We don't see anything too interesting at this point so we pass. Server floats off. 10 mins later returns with our check. No charge for the mistaken Burrata nor my never seen or heard from again appetizer I had ordered. We are just as confused as our server seems to be. If the restaurant had been a madhouse I would have understood a kitchen mistake, but even the couple behind us, who had started long before us, were just receiving their dinners. It had such good potential: comfy, pretty and a little sexy atmosphere. Nice tight menu with good options for dinner or even just sharing with friends. I hope it was just an off night for our server or the kitchen cause it is well positioned to be a great upscale neighborhood place.

What a fabulous experience! My wife and I went in for dinner last weekend and couldn't have had a better time!! We were sat immediately upon arrival and within seconds our server....a charming little guy....greeted us and offered to decant the bottle of wine we had brought in. He even commented on the vintage (05 Burgundy...Mmmm)! We then asked for recommendations on apps and entrees as we hadn't been here before and were blown away by his selections. Personally I can't say EVERYTHING on the menu is great, but the Meatballs, Mussels, Cauliflower salad and Trout were all spot on!! In between courses an Italian looking gentleman (i assume manager?) stopped by our table and inquired about dinner and mentioned that the next time we came in we needed to try some of the impressive selections they have on the reserve list. A request i rarely agree to but in this case...why not??? After dinner we adjourned to the bar for a cocktail and my wife immediately took to the bartender! "Murph" as he calls himself was hilarious and a veritable encyclopedia of information on Bourbon!! Before we knew it it was past midnight and we had to get home to the kids, but if you're in Lincoln Park and are looking for a great date night spot, Willow Room lives up to the hype!!

We had a reservation for 8 pm but they did not have a table available. We had to wait 40 minutes and the bar was super busy. When we were finally seated the food took 35 minutes and they forgot the appetizers. In the end the food was great but the service needs improvement.

Our time at the Willow Room was a disaster. Our friends who flew in 700 miles for dinner made the best of a horrible situation. First, we had to wait over 20 minutes past our reservation time to get a table, after being brought downstairs and a server telling the hostess we couldn't sit there because a large group was coming in 90 minutes. Then we waited at the bar where both bartenders ignored us for 10 minutes while trying to order drinks. We were finally seated and our waiter was very nice...but after an hour of being at the restaurant we realized we still didn't have any food, and that's when our entrees arrived prior to our appetizers. Even though we told them we no longer needed the appetizers, they still brought them and comp'd them...along with a round of drinks we had while waiting for our food to arrive. Every other table in the restaurant seemed to not be having the same issues we were having and we did ask if we were being punk'd but no one on staff would confirm our appearance on an upcoming reality show...and we never did manage to have a manager come over and apologize for the entire evening.
We come here often,  especially for brunch and absolutely love it! Great atmosphere, food and service!

I went here with my family, there were six of us. We ordered 4 burgers , 1 trout and a steak. We waited one hour and only the steak arrived. We asked the waitress/waiter multiple times as to where our food was. Of course we assumed that there would be some sort of apitzer so eventually my grandmother went and asked for bread and butter. They said we "don't normally serve that". They then came out with a microwaved plate of bread and a scoop of butter. The service was terrible and after the hour passed still there was no food, we left and went to a much more reliable and amazing restaurant. Therefore ruining our image of this restaurant.
Excellent atmosphere, staff was awesome and so was the food.. Great experience.

My wife and I popped in here for brunch on Saturday and had a great experience. This place serves a great Bloody Mary (I went with meat, wife went veggie) - not too spicy, solid mix. I had the Hex Toast and it was awesome. Filling without being overwhelming. My wife had the Crab Omelette and loved it. There were a few dishes that I wanted to try, so I wouldn't mind coming back over the summer. Try it.
